						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in survey No. 26.</p>						

						<p>Velugōṭi-Venkaṭapatirāya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1539, Dundubhi, Māgha ba. 10.</hi> However, the Śaka year is irregular in which case the other details of the date may be corresponds to 1623 A.D., February 14, Friday.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It mentions the village Niṇḍali given as <hi rend="italic">amara</hi> to Voḍepalle Raṅgappa by the chief and also records a gift of some <hi rend="italic">mānya</hi> to him for the upkeep of the tank in the village.</p>						

						</summary>
